sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client (Browser)
    participant AM as AuthMiddleware
    participant AC as AuthController
    participant AS as AuthService
    participant AR as AuthRepository
    participant DB as Database

    Note over C,DB: 0 · Cadastro inicial — RF027

    C->>+AC: 0a. POST /auth/register/manager { name, email, password }
    Note over AC: Rota pública — sem requireAuth
    AC->>+AS: registerManager(name, email, password)
    AS->>AS: bcrypt.hash(password, 10)
    AS->>+AR: createManager({ name, email, password_hash })
    AR->>+DB: INSERT INTO managers (name, email, password_hash)
    DB-->>-AR: manager { id, name, email, role: "manager" }
    AR-->>-AS: manager
    AS-->>-AC: manager
    AC-->>-C: 201 { id, name, email, role: "manager" }

    C->>+AC: 0b. POST /auth/register/auditor { name, email, password }
    AC->>+AS: registerAuditor(name, email, password)
    AS->>AS: bcrypt.hash(password, 10)
    AS->>+AR: createAuditor({ name, email, password_hash })
    AR->>+DB: INSERT INTO auditors (name, email, password_hash)
    DB-->>-AR: auditor { id, name, email, role: "auditor" }
    AR-->>-AS: auditor
    AS-->>-AC: auditor
    AC-->>-C: 201 { id, name, email, role: "auditor" }

    alt Email ja cadastrado
        AR-->>AS: conflict
        AS-->>AC: 409 { error: "Email ja cadastrado" }
        AC-->>C: 409 { error: "Email ja cadastrado" }
    end

    Note over C,DB: 1 · Login — RF027 · RN38 · RN39 · RN41

    C->>+AC: 1. POST /auth/login { email, password }
    AC->>+AS: 2. login(email, password)
    AS->>+AR: 3. findByEmail(email)
    AR->>+DB: 4. SELECT * FROM managers/auditors WHERE email = $1
    DB-->>-AR: 5. user row (id, name, email, password_hash, role)
    AR-->>-AS: 6. user | null
    AS->>AS: 7. bcrypt.compare(password, hash)
    AS->>AS: 8. signAccessToken(payload) — exp 15min
    AS->>AS: 9. signRefreshToken() — exp 7d
    AS->>+AR: 10. saveRefreshToken(SHA-256(refreshToken), userId, role)
    AR->>+DB: 11. INSERT INTO refresh_tokens (token_hash, manager_id/auditor_id, expires_at)
    DB-->>-AR: 12. ok
    AR-->>-AS: 13. saved
    AS-->>-AC: 14. { accessToken, refreshToken }
    AC-->>-C: 15. 200 — Set-Cookie: accessToken (HttpOnly, 15min) + refreshToken (HttpOnly, 7d)

    alt Credenciais inválidas
        AS-->>AC: 401 { error: "Credenciais inválidas" }
        AC-->>C: 401 { error: "Credenciais inválidas" }
    end

    Note over C,DB: 2 · Requisição autenticada (API) — requireAuth

    C->>+AM: 16. GET /audit/shifts/:id/status — Authorization: Bearer <accessToken>
    AM->>AM: 17. verifyAccessToken(token)
    alt Token válido
        AM->>AM: 18. req.user = { id, email, role, name }
        AM-->>C: next() — requisição prossegue ao Controller
    else Token ausente ou expirado
        AM-->>-C: 401 { error: "Token de acesso inválido ou expirado" }
    end

    Note over C,DB: 3 · Renovação de token (SSR) — requirePageAuth

    C->>+AM: 19. GET /audit (page route) — Cookie: accessToken (expirado)
    AM->>AM: 20. verifyAccessToken(accessToken) → falha
    AM->>+AS: 21. AuthService.refresh(refreshToken)
    AS->>+AR: 22. findByHash(SHA-256(refreshToken))
    AR->>+DB: 23. SELECT * FROM refresh_tokens WHERE token_hash = $1 AND revoked_at IS NULL
    DB-->>-AR: 24. token row
    AR-->>-AS: 25. tokenRecord
    AS->>+AR: 26. revokeToken(id) — preenche revoked_at
    AR->>+DB: 27. UPDATE refresh_tokens SET revoked_at = NOW()
    DB-->>-AR: 28. ok
    AR-->>-AS: 29. revoked
    AS->>AS: 30. signAccessToken + signRefreshToken novos
    AS->>+AR: 31. saveRefreshToken(novo hash)
    AR->>+DB: 32. INSERT novo refresh_token
    DB-->>-AR: 33. ok
    AR-->>-AS: 34. saved
    AS-->>-AM: 35. { accessToken, refreshToken }
    AM->>AM: 36. Set-Cookie com novos tokens + req.user preenchido
    AM-->>-C: 37. página renderizada normalmente

    alt refreshToken ausente ou revogado
        AS-->>AM: null
        AM-->>C: redirect /login
    end

    Note over C,DB: 4 · Logout — RF027 · RN40 · RN41

    C->>+AC: 38. POST /auth/logout { refreshToken? } — Cookie: refreshToken
    AC->>+AS: 39. logout(refreshToken)
    AS->>AS: 40. SHA-256(refreshToken)
    AS->>+AR: 41. revokeToken(token_hash)
    AR->>+DB: 42. UPDATE refresh_tokens SET revoked_at = NOW() WHERE token_hash = $1
    DB-->>-AR: 43. ok
    AR-->>-AS: 44. revoked
    AS-->>-AC: 45. ok
    AC-->>-C: 46. 200 — Clear-Cookie: accessToken + refreshToken
    Note over C: accessToken expira naturalmente em até 15min
